page.title: 01Land's End
page.content: This block contains one of the most famous and most visited parts of the {British Isles}-the {Land's End}which is,of course,the most westerly point of mainland {Britain.} At{Land's End}there are several un- usual rocks like{The Irish Lady and Dr {Syntax's Head.}They are called these names because of their shape.There are many other rocks like these at{Land's {End. There are also three exhibitions_one is about{Sennen's}past, one is about the{Life Boat}and{Coast Guard}and one is about{Worzil Gummage. Northeastwards along the cliff is an ancient primitive castle about 3000 years old called{Maen Castle. There is also a lot of wild iife at {Land's End.}Some examples of flowers are Sea Pink and Sea Campion. Some common birds are Gannets and Seagulls.
